# =============================================================================
# Web client (Vite) — public `VITE_*` variables only (`apps/web-client/.env.example`)
# =============================================================================
# Vite inlines every `VITE_*` value into the browser bundle. Anyone can read them
# from the built assets or DevTools.
#
# Never put here:
#   • R2 / S3 API tokens, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, MinIO root passwords
#   • Messaging-service JWT signing secrets, database passwords, SendGrid keys
#   • Any credential that should authenticate *to your API* or *to object storage*
# Those belong only in messaging-service / Docker / infra env (see `infra/.env.example`).
#
# Local overrides: copy the lines you need into `.env.development.local` or
# `.env.production.local` (gitignored — see `apps/web-client/.gitignore`).
# Defaults for dev/prod are layered from `.env.development` / `.env.production`.
# =============================================================================

# --- REST + Socket.IO base (`src/common/utils/apiConfig.ts`) -----------------
# Relative path = same origin as the SPA (Vite proxy or nginx forwards `/v1`).
# Use an absolute URL only when the API + Socket.IO host differs from the page.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=/v1
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/v1

# --- Public media URL prefix (optional; `src/common/utils/mediaPublicUrl.ts`) -
# Used only to build **browser-displayable** URLs for object keys (path-style:
# `{base}/{bucket}/{encodedKey...}`). Must match how messaging-service exposes
# public reads (`S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` + `S3_BUCKET`), if you use public buckets /
# R2 public dev domains. The bucket **name** is not a secret (it appears in URLs).
# Omit both vars to skip client-built public URLs (thread attachments fall back to text).
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://pub.example.com
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9000
# VITE_S3_BUCKET=messaging-media

# --- Chat / profile uploads — client-side max size before presign (`apiConfig.ts`) -
# Optional cap before `postMediaPresign` / avatar presign is called. Default when
# unset: 104857600 bytes (100 MiB). Invalid or non-positive values fall back to default.
# VITE_MEDIA_UPLOAD_MAX_BYTES=52428800

# --- Device key sync page size (optional; `deviceKeySyncLimits.ts`) -----------
# Integer 1–100; default 100 when unset.
# VITE_DEVICE_KEY_SYNC_PAGE_LIMIT=100

# --- Sign-out: revoke server device row (optional; `logoutDeviceRevocation.ts`) -
# When `true`, logout calls `DELETE /users/me/devices/:deviceId`. Default: omit / false.
# VITE_REVOKE_DEVICE_ON_LOGOUT=true

# --- WebRTC ICE (optional; `webrtcIceServers.ts`) -----------------------------
# STUN hostnames are public by design. TURN username and credential are also shipped
# in the client bundle — use **dev-only** or **short-lived** TURN credentials, not
# production secrets shared with server-only systems.
# VITE_WEBRTC_STUN_URLS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302
# VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_URLS=turn:127.0.0.1:3478
# VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_USERNAME=dev
# VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_CREDENTIAL=local-dev-secret

# --- Debug flags (development only) ------------------------------------------
# VITE_DEBUG_PEER_DECRYPT=true
# VITE_DEBUG_MESSAGE_DISPLAY=true
